{{#> layouts/simple }}

  {{> navbar}}

  {{#> hero title=(concat "<span class='fw-bold text-primary'>Volunteering</span> @ " siteMetadata.name "</span>")}}
    <p class="lead mb-4">
      <span class="fw-semibold">{{siteMetadata.name}}</span> sells equipment on eBay that is not useful for low-income or community groups.
      These items may be bulky, faulty, vintage, enterprise equipment, one of a kind, or end-of-life equipment.
      Laptops listed have issues or have marks and scratches. Excess stock is also sold.
    </p>
  {{/hero}}

  <section class="container py-5">

    <!-- Volunteering at-->
    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Volunteering at <span class="fw-semibold">{{siteMetadata.name}}</span></h2>

    <p class="mb-3">
      <span class="fw-semibold">{{siteMetadata.name}}</span>’s volunteers range from technical experts to hobbyists and come from many cultural and linguistic backgrounds and ages.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-3">
      Are you interested in recycling electronic equipment, supporting welfare and community-based organisations,
      and would you like to help enable access to computing for people on low incomes?
    </p>

    <p class="mb-3">
      We use open-source software on our computers (not Windows) as we are committed to using free and open-source software.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-5">

    <!-- Volunteer Commitment -->
    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Volunteer Commitment</h2>

    <p class="mb-3">
      Volunteers must be able to commit to one or more shifts a fortnight and be keen to work in a team of like-minded people in a friendly atmosphere.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-3">
      Volunteers will need to log in to our website regularly to add their name to a roster and check for updates to documentation and our to-do lists via the volunteer dashboard.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-4">
      All volunteers are expected to contribute to the daily housekeeping of the premises to ensure all areas are kept clean and tidy.
    </p>

    <p class="mb-3">
      If you have experience with Linux, that will serve you well at Computerbank; however, this is not a prerequisite for all volunteers, as there are plenty of other ways for you to contribute!
    </p>

    <hr class="my-5">

    <!-- Apply to Volunteer -->
    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Ready to Apply?</h2>

    <p class="mb-3">
      You can apply right now via our website using the <a href="#">Volunteer Application form</a>.
      Tell us about your skills and ideally include your résumé.
      We will invite you to an information session where we can discuss volunteering.
      Information sessions are held regularly.
    </p>

    <!-- Images Row -->
    <div class="row mb-5">
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <img src="images/build-room.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" alt="Build Room">
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <img src="images/cloning-station.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" alt="Cloning Station">
      </div>
      <div class="col-md-4">
        <img src="images/build-desk-2.jpg" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm" alt="Build Desk">
      </div>
    </div>

    <hr class="my-5">

    <!-- Volunteer Positions -->
    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Volunteer Positions Available</h2>

    <!-- Front Desk and Customer Service -->
    <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3 fw-bold">Front Desk and Customer Service</h3>

    <p class="mb-3">
      A great way to get some IT retail experience. Volunteers who successfully complete at least six months of solid volunteering with us may ask for a reference.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-3 mb-2 fw-bold">Duties</h4>
    <p class="mb-3">
      Duties include customer service, answering phones, and explaining to in-store customers about our low-cost Linux computers and answering any questions.
      Assistance with other areas as required.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-3 mb-2 fw-bold">Volunteer Requirements</h4>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Volunteers must be comfortable with Linux and Linux desktops, preferably using it on a regular basis.
      Volunteers must be willing to become familiar with the Computerbank customised distribution desktop.
    </p>

    <!-- Technical/Buildroom and Warehouse -->
    <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3 fw-bold">Technical/Buildroom and Warehouse</h3>

    <p class="mb-3">
      We pride ourselves on building computers that are reliable and fully functional.
      To achieve this, all computers are built according to our in-house procedures, and documentation is maintained at each stage.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-3 mb-2 fw-bold">Duties</h4>
    <p class="mb-3">
      The main function is the building of computers for sale following our in-house procedures.
      Duties also include assessing donated computers, wiping hard drives, recycling computers and components, and some warehouse housekeeping.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-3 mb-2 fw-bold">Volunteer Requirements</h4>
    <p class="mb-4">
      Familiarity with GNOME/Mate and Linux is essential, along with component assembly.
      Familiarity with hardware is always useful too. We need people with command line skills,
      people who can manage files from the command line, and know the difference between a regular prompt and a hash prompt.
      Programming skills are not a requirement.
    </p>

    <!-- In-house and Telephone User Support -->
    <h3 class="mt-4 mb-3 fw-bold">In-house and Telephone User Support</h3>

    <p class="mb-3">
      Most of our users **do not** use the command line, nor are they expected to.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-3 mb-2 fw-bold">Duties</h4>
    <p class="mb-3">
      Involves providing user support to new users and troubleshooting specific problems.
    </p>

    <h4 class="mt-3 mb-2 fw-bold">Requirements</h4>
    <p class="mb-4">
      This role requires patience and excellent knowledge of the command line, Linux, and Computerbank’s customised distribution.
    </p>

    <hr class="my-5">

    <!-- Other Functions -->
    <h2 class="mt-5 mb-3 fw-bold">Other Functions</h2>

    <p class="mb-3">
      Volunteers also have the opportunity to be involved in other tasks required for the general running of Computerbank, such as:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-group list-group-flush mb-4">
      <li class="list-group-item">Sales database management and development</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">Website management</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">New distribution version development</li>
      <li class="list-group-item">Internal network management</li>
    </ul>



  </section>

{{/layouts/simple}}